<section id="subversion-commands">
<title>Useful Subversion Commands</title>

  <section id="subversion-commands-list">
  <title>Directory listing</title>
  <para>
  The Subversion repository structure is not evident by doing a unix
  <command>ls</command> at <filename>/misc/inca/subversion</filename>.
  To see the repository structure, use the <command>list</command> command.
	</para>

  <example>
  <title>List directory structure (from cuzco.sdsc.edu)</title>
  <screen>
  svn list file:///misc/inca/subversion
  </screen>
  </example>
  
  <example>
  <title>List directory structure via SSH</title>
  <screen>
  svn list svn+ssh://cuzco.sdsc.edu/misc/inca/subversion
  </screen>
  </example>
  
  </section>

  <section id="subversion-commands-mkdir">
  <title>Create a directory</title>
  <para>
  To create a new directory <filename>docs</filename> under
  <filename>inca/trunk</filename>:
	</para>
  
  <example>
  <title>Within an existing Subversion checkout</title>
  <screen>
  svn mkdir docs
  </screen>
  </example>
  
  <example>
  <title>Outside of a Subversion checkout</title>
  <screen>
  svn mkdir svn+ssh://cuzco.sdsc.edu/misc/inca/subversion/inca/trunk/docs
  </screen>
  </example>
  
  </section>

  <section id="subversion-commands-import">
  <title>Import a directory</title>
  <para>
  To import a directory <filename>docs</filename> under
  <filename>inca/trunk</filename>, create a temporary directory 
  <filename>tmpdir</filename> outside of your Subversion checkout.
	</para>
  
  <screen>
  mkdir tmpdir
  </screen>
  
	<para>
  Then move <filename>docs</filename> under <filename>tmpdir</filename> and
  import it.
	</para>
  
  <screen>
  mv docs tmpdir
  cd tmpdir
  svn import . svn+ssh://cuzco.sdsc.edu/misc/inca/subversion/inca/trunk
  </screen>
  
	<para>
  You can then verify that the directory exists by listing it.
	</para>
  
  <screen>
  svn list svn+ssh://cuzco.sdsc.edu/misc/inca/subversion/inca/trunk
  </screen>
  
  </section>
  
  <section id="subversion-commands-relocate">
  <title>Change repository location</title>

  <para>
	If your Subversion repository location changes, you can use the 
	<command>--relocate</command> option to the <command>switch</command>
	command.  The following example shows how to deal with the Subversion
	repository on <filename>inca.sdsc.edu</filename> being moved to
	<filename>cuzco.sdsc.edu</filename>.
	</para>

	<screen>
  svn switch --relocate svn+ssh://inca.sdsc.edu/misc/inca/subversion/inca/trunk\
  svn+ssh://cuzco.sdsc.edu/misc/inca/subversion/inca/trunk
	</screen>

	</section>

</section>
